  "notes": "Hiri Motu (Police Motu) — a simplified, pidginised variety of Motu and one of the three official languages of Papua New Guinea. Latin script, phonemic spelling with a five-vowel system /i ɛ a ɔ u/. ⟨v⟩ is the voiced bilabial fricative /β/; ⟨r⟩ is a tap /ɾ/. Syllables are open (CV); consonant clusters do not occur natively.",
